author: CNN

title: RFK Jr. compares Kirk to Jesus Christ

author: CNN
description: California on Saturday became the first state to bar most law enforcement officers—including federal immigration agents—from covering their faces while on duty, after Gov. Gavin Newsom signed the bill into law. The move was quickly condemned by Trump administration officials.   #CNN #News
title: Newsom: Federal raids are 'like a dystopian sci-fi movie'

author: CNN
description: Massive crowds have filled State Farm Stadium near Phoenix, Arizona, for the memorial service of slain conservative activist Charlie Kirk. With the stadium near capacity, some attendees were directed to overflow areas, and mourners began lining up as early as 2:30 a.m. Glendale police estimate that more than 200,000 people may try to attend. CNN correspondent Artlette Saenz reports from Glendale, while Washington bureau chief David Chalian and senior White House correspondent Kristen Holmes join Boris Sanchez and Pamela Brown to provide broader coverage.   #CNN #News
title: Trump: Kirk service will 'celebrate the life of a great man'

author: CNN
description: Locked out of power in Washington, Senate Minority Leader Chuck Schumer and top Democrats are challenging President Donald Trump over this month’s government funding deadline, demanding that Republicans extend billions in expiring Obamacare subsidies. CNN’s Dana Bash is joined by Alex Thompson, Axios national political correspondent and CNN political analyst; Kristen Holmes, CNN senior White House correspondent; and political commentators Brad Todd, GOP strategist, and a former DNC communications director.   #CNN #News
title: Schumer: We need to get something done to relieve the distress the American people are in

author: CNN
description: Inside Arizona’s State Farm Stadium, tens of thousands are gathering today for a memorial service honoring conservative activist Charlie Kirk, who was shot and killed 11 days ago during a campus event at Utah Valley University. The 31-year-old’s memorial features top figures from the Trump-aligned movement, including former President Donald Trump, Vice President J.D. Vance, and Kirk’s widow, Erica Kirk, who has stepped into her late husband’s leadership role. On Friday, the House overwhelmingly passed a resolution condemning Kirk’s assassination and political violence, while praising him as a “courageous American patriot.” The measure passed 310 to 58, with Democrats deeply divided. CNN’s Dana Bash speaks with Scott Jennings and David Axelrod about the impact.   #CNN #News
title: Memorial service draws thousands in tribute to Charlie Kirk

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump on Saturday escalated pressure on Attorney General Pam Bondi, urging her to bring charges against political opponents including New York AG Letitia James, Senator Adam Schiff, and former FBI Director James Comey. He called them “guilty as hell” and faulted Bondi for what he sees as inaction. Senate Democratic leader Chuck Schumer responds in an interview with CNN’s Dana Bash   #CNN #News
title: Trump pushes AG Bondi to ramp up justice department action

author: CNN
description: Key provisions of the 2018 farm bill are set to expire at the end of the month, with many farmers facing a gap in federal support until President Trump’s proposed replacement bill takes effect late next year. The looming lapse comes as US farmers warn they are nearing a breaking point, squeezed by volatile weather, rising costs, and the lingering impact of Trump’s tariffs. CNN’s Boris Sanchez spoke with John Boyd Jr., founder and president of the National Black Farmers Association.  #CNN #News
title: US farmers warn of breaking point as harvest meets trade war

description: Stock markets ended the week reaching new highs for two straight days. The Dow, Nasdaq and the S&P 500 all clocking records on Thursday and Friday. CNN's Boris Sanchez is joined by economist Betsey Stevenson to discuss.   #CNN #News
title: Markets climb after Fed steps in to support weak job market
